metadata.name: Case of the Mondays
metadata.description:
The Case of the Mondays refers to the feeling of depression, anxiety, or dread that some people experience at the start of a new work week. It is often associated with the feeling of being overwhelmed or burned out from the demands of work or personal responsibilities. The phrase "Case of the Mondays" is often used humorously to describe this feeling, but it can also be a serious issue for those who struggle with mental health on a regular basis. It is important to find healthy ways to manage these feelings, such as taking breaks, getting enough sleep, and finding activities that bring joy and relaxation.
